cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with a multi-drone setting and proposes an auction-based mechanism to control the charging schedule. This falls under the domain of multi-agent systems.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - Drones are a type of robot, and the paper deals with designing a charging mechanism for them. Hence, it can be categorized under robotics.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning algorithms to learn the distribution of the number of drones participating in the auction. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a solution for outdoor ad-hoc battery charging for drones, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a mechanism to control the charging schedule of drones, which can be categorized under systems and control.
